The update aims to enhance user experience and provide more diverse creative tools for Canva's large user base.

data.title: Sigma, leader in AI data apps, inducted into JPMorganChase Hall of Innovation for tech driving business value.
data.description: In San Francisco, Sigma, a prominent AI data applications leader, has been honored by being inducted into the JPMorganChase Hall of Innovation. The prestigious accolade was received during the Technology Innovation Symposium held by the company. Sigma's innovative technology, powered by AI, offers enterprise analytics teams the advantage of speedy and secure data analysis. With Sigma, users can efficiently analyze and construct applications using live data, which includes the consolidation of billions of records and unstructured document analysis.

data.title: RoarFun™ utilizes Formula Simulator for brand activation in prestigious retail space, engaging thousands for immersive experience.
data.description: RoarFun™, an entertainment tech firm, demonstrates that emotion is the top factor for engagement. The company converted a section of a top retail spot into an immersive Formula experience, captivating thousands of visitors.

data.title: Jennifer Taylor named one of "NC Lawyers Weekly" 2025 '50 Most Influential Women'. Award celebrates women leaders in NC.
data.description: A recognition has been awarded to female leaders making significant contributions in the legal and business sectors in North Carolina. Taking place in Durham, N.C. on Oct. 29, 2025, The Law Offices of James Scott Farrin is pleased to share that Partner Jennifer Taylor has been chosen for the prestigious "North Carolina Lawyers Weekly's" award.

data.title: Catalyx Space raises $5.4M for orbital logistics to make downmass function as scheduled logistics service.
data.description: Catalyx is developing a comprehensive backend system for space operations, encompassing hardware, software, and logistical operations for both upmass and downmass. This system aims to streamline space missions, making launches scheduled and predictable. However, the challenge lies in making downmass as reliable as upmass. Catalyx is revolutionizing the return journey by transforming it into a service that can be booked, enhancing efficiency and accessibility in space missions.

data.title: Survey finds 1 in 3 Gen Z workers yelled at boss, prefer authenticity over professionalism in workplace behavior.
data.description: According to a recent survey by ResumeTemplates.com, 1,200 full-time Gen Z workers in Seattle have indicated a preference for authenticity over conventional professionalism in the workplace. The study highlights a shift in the attitudes of young professionals, with a significant percentage challenging traditional norms.

data.title: Berger Montague PC is investigating KinderCare Learning Companies, Inc.'s Board of Directors for fiduciary duty breaches (NYSE: KLC).
data.description: A law firm in Philadelphia, Berger Montague PC, is informing shareholders of KinderCare Learning Companies, Inc. about an inquiry into the Company's Board of Directors for possible violations of fiduciary responsibilities towards KinderCare and its stakeholders. The investigation aims to scrutinize the Board's actions to ensure they acted in the best interests of the company and its shareholders. Further details regarding the investigation or any findings were not disclosed in the news. It is essential for shareholders of KinderCare to stay informed and vigilant regarding this development to protect their investments.

data.title: Historic milestone: ASL now has a digital dictionary in sign language. Visit TheASLDictionary.com.
data.description: In a groundbreaking development, a digital dictionary has been launched in American Sign Language (ASL) for the first time, created by and for the ASL community. This innovative resource can be accessed at TheASLDictionary.com, marking a significant milestone in ASL education and accessibility.

data.title: Melissa Sisneros appointed as Senior VP of CEIS | Government, role to drive growth and innovation.
data.description: In Albuquerque, New Mexico on October 30, 2025, Critical Energy Infrastructure Services (CEIS) has disclosed the selection of Melissa Sisneros as the Senior Vice President of CEIS | Government. This key position aims to spearhead the company's expansion and advancements.

data.title: Berger Moving & Storage of St. Paul named Allied's 2025 Agent of the Year. Carl Berger founded in 1910.
data.description: A moving company based in Oakbrook Terrace, Illinois, announced on October 30, 2025, that Berger Moving & Storage in St. Paul, Minnesota, has been honored as the 2025 Agent of the Year. Allied Van Lines, Inc., a renowned global moving company, recognized Berger Moving & Storage for its outstanding performance. Established in 1910 by Mr. Carl Berger, the company stood out amongst others to receive this prestigious accolade. This recognition highlights Berger Moving & Storage's commitment to excellence in the moving industry.

data.title: Toll Brothers to launch 55+ luxury home community in Jacksonville, FL called Regency at EverRange with resort-style amenities.
data.description: The upcoming Regency at EverRange development will provide residents with a low-maintenance lifestyle and access to luxurious amenities within the EverRange master plan community. This new development aims to offer a high-quality living experience with an array of resort-style features. The project is set to encompass a range of housing options and communal facilities, catering to various preferences and needs. Residents can expect a vibrant community atmosphere alongside convenient services and recreational opportunities.

data.title: Dr. Nikolas P. Tsakos of TEN honored for his maritime industry contributions and philanthropy at "Chrysanthemum Ball" Gala.
data.description: In Greece, on October 30, 2025, Dr. Nikolas P. Tsakos, the Founder & CEO of Tsakos Energy Navigation ("TEN"), was recognized at the prestigious "Chrysanthemum Ball" Gala in New York. This event is arranged by the Philanthropic Brotherhood of the Archdiocesan Cathedral of the Holy Trinity and is known for its social and charitable significance. Dr. Tsakos received this honor for his contributions to the industry.

data.title: Event hosted by Anthony Lamacchia for brokers to learn about acquisitions after acquiring 11 companies in 26 months.
data.description: Discover how Lamacchia Realty Broker/Owner, Anthony Lamacchia, successfully acquired 11 companies within just 26 months at the upcoming event in Norwalk, Conn., on October 30, 2025. Attendees will have the opportunity to connect with industry peers, as well as gain insights into the M&A process by receiving a comprehensive playbook. Don't miss this two-day event focused on "Growth Through Acquisitions" to learn from Lamacchia's experiences and strategies.

data.title: Zum recognized in 2025 Reuters Awards for improving student transportation safety. Highly Commended. #innovation
data.description: Zūm, a prominent player in modern student transportation based in REDWOOD CITY, Calif., was recently acknowledged for its efforts to enhance safety, efficiency, and grid resiliency in student transportation. The company received the prestigious "Highly Commended" recognition in Product Innovation. This significant achievement, announced on Oct. 30, 2025, showcases Zūm's dedication to innovation and excellence in the industry. The recognition reflects the company's commitment to providing safe and efficient transportation solutions, ultimately improving the overall quality of student transportation experiences.
